        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 25 at 6:31PM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 630 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
West End-Cobb Town, moving northeast at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Ragland, Anniston, Munford, Coleman Lake And Campground, Choccolocco,
Talladega Superspeedway, Anniston Regional Airport, Edwardsville,
Cobb City, Blue Mountain, Heflin, Cobb Town, Sulphur Springs,
Jenifer, Hobson City, Alexandria, Reaves, Talladega Municipal
Airport, Jacksonville, and Jacksonville State University.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
